-/// Source files declared on an extension are recorded by absolute path; their
-/// bytes are read from disk during snapshot creation and never embedded in the
-/// final binary. With a startup snapshot, the source is reachable via the
-/// snapshot bytes (for `esm`/`js`) or the residual lazy table emitted by the
-/// snapshot build (for `lazy_loaded_*`).
+/// kabegame patch: embed extension source bytes into the binary via
+/// `include_str!` (`mode=included`) instead of recording an absolute build-time
+/// path read from disk at runtime (`mode=loaded`).
+///
+/// Upstream deno_core defaults to `mode=loaded`: every `esm`/`js` source is a
+/// `LoadedFromFsDuringSnapshot(<abs build path>)`, expecting a V8 startup
+/// snapshot to have captured its bytes. Deno always snapshots, so it never
+/// touches disk at runtime.
+///
+/// kabegame runs snapshotless (`startup_snapshot: None`), so `extension_set`'s
+/// "not in snapshot → load every declared file from disk" path reads each
+/// source from its absolute build-machine path at `JsRuntime::new` time. That
+/// happens to work on desktop (build machine == run machine) but breaks under
+/// cross-compilation: on an Android device the recorded paths are the Linux
+/// host's cargo-registry paths, which don't exist → `read_to_string` ENOENT →
+/// "Failed to initialize a JsRuntime: No such file or directory (os error 2)".
+///
+/// Because `[patch.crates-io] deno_core` routes `deno_web`/`deno_crypto`/
+/// `deno_webidl`'s `extension!` expansion through this crate too, flipping the
+/// default to `included` embeds all of their sources (and kabegame_v8's) at
+/// their own compile time — no runtime disk access, and desktop release builds
+/// stop depending on the build tree being present. This matches deno_core's
+/// pre-refactor `#[cfg(not(feature = "include_js_files_for_snapshotting"))]`
+/// default. kabegame never builds a snapshot, so unconditional embedding is safe.
 #[doc(hidden)]
 #[macro_export]
 macro_rules! __extension_include_js_files_detect {
-  ($($rest:tt)*) => { $crate::__extension_include_js_files_inner!(mode=loaded, $($rest)*) };
+  ($($rest:tt)*) => { $crate::__extension_include_js_files_inner!(mode=included, $($rest)*) };
 }
 
